<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,366,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1302,1328]" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Bai &amp; Heiss &amp; Cai, 2020" authorityName="Bai &amp; Heiss &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2020" box="[338,490,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Neolibiocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[338,490,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Neolibiocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[497,598,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bai, Heiss &amp; Cai, 2018" authorityName="Bai, Heiss &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2018" box="[739,1168,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Paralibiocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[739,902,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Paralibiocoris</emphasis>
Bai, Heiss &amp; Cai, 2018
</taxonomicName>
, which is also described from 
<collectingRegion box="[215,296,1339,1365]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Hainan</collectingRegion>
Island. It differs however by obtuse anterolateral angles of pronotum, not produced over collar, the elongate conical shape of median thoracic sclerite with granulate surface and longitudinal sulcus, by large shiny callus on vltg VII of male and heart shaped pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[745,859,1410,1437]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–4" captionStart-1="FIGURES 5–15" captionStartId-0="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox-0="[188,1403,191,1910]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1428,190,1880]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@2.[176,1411,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–4. Neolibiocoris obtusus gen. nov., sp. nov. 1–2, holotype male; 3–4, paratype female. 1, 3, dorsal view; 2, 4, ventral view. Scale bar = 1 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 5–15. Neolibiocoris obtusus gen. nov., sp. nov. 5–10, different body parts; 11–12, pygophore in dorsal and lateral views; 13–15, right paramere. 5, 6, 9, 10, holotype male; 7, 8, paratype female; 5, 7, 9, 11, dorsal view; 6, 8, 10, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm for 5–12; 0.1 mm for 13–15." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296576" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296578" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4296576/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4296578/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Figs. 1-15</figureCitation>
) (vs. anterolateral angles of pronotum rounded and produced over collar, median thoracic sclerite bottle shaped with smooth surface, by small oblique callus on vltg VII of male and conically produced pygophore (Figs. 39,40).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
